<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 9:55PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Valley
County through 1100 PM MDT...
At 954 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles northwest of St. Marie, or 22 miles southwest of Opheim, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Opheim, Port Of Opheim, St. Marie, Thoeny, Baylor, Glentana and
Larslan.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
